been treated as second-class citizens.
Clinical psychology is making the painful dis-
covery that academic departments of psychology in the faculty of arts and sciences are not the best places in which to train professionals and that the psychiatric setting is an unsatisfactory place to learn the ideology of practice. But it is hard to change tradition, even if tradition is only 25 years
