Qualitatively, what seems to occur is this. Chains which converge on the target principally by using geographic information reach his hometown or the surrounding areas readily, but once there often circulate before en- tering the target's circle of acquaintances. There is no available information to narrow the field of potential contacts which an individual might have within the town. Such additional information as a list of local organizations
