            <Text>#### The Paradigmatic experiments
&lt;!--\newthought{The ‘Junior high’ version}--&gt; of the scientific method tells us that to be science, one must observe-hypothesis-experiment-repeat. This simply isn’t true. Science uses a number of different methods, and not everything takes the form of the the classic *experimentum crucis* that we were taught in seventh grade.
&lt;!--\begin{marginfigure}
 \begin{center}
