Constructing good hypotheses and good questions to test hypothesis can be challenging, especially in psychology and psychiatry. In this section, we’ll introduce some basic terminology regarding scientific reasoning and discuss a few model studies---those we call ‘paradigms’---that have influenced how science has progressed.</Text>
