            <Title>Narrative</Title>
            <Text>This events that lead up to the clash over the validity of scientific studies of the human mind span countries and continents. Ideas flow quickly---even in the 18th and 19th centuries, so understanding how the peculiar American definitions of mental health and illness came about require a bit of explanation. </Text>
